Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and slice into thin strips.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, fry the @chorizo{100%g} and bell pepper until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the black beans and @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, if required.

Fry for ~{1%minute} then add the @passata{1%pack}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Stir through the @chipotle paste{1%sachet}. Add a splash of @water{to taste}, if required.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Meanwhile, cut the @tomato{2}(diced into 1cm cubes) into 1cm cubes.

Halve, peel and chop the @shallot{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Toss the tomato and shallot together in a #bowl{}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop the @tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Serve the beans and tomato salsa separately.

Divide the tortillas between plates and top your own at the table.

Sprinkle with a generous helping of @grated cheese{50%g}.

Drizzle over the @creme fraiche{65%g} and @BBQ sauce{2%sachets}.

> These tortillas are a family favourite recipe with lashings of melted cheese,
> slightly spiced chorizo and softened veg for a filling that's too good to pass up.
> Refreshment comes in the form of tomato salsa and zesty creme fraiche.